  // =============================================================================
  // FETAL ANOMALY SCAN (18-22 WEEKS)
  // =============================================================================
  {
    id: 'fetal-anomaly-scan',
    subjectId: 'obgyn',
    subspecialtyId: 'obgyn-fetal-medicine',
    name: 'Fetal Anomaly Scan',
    slug: 'fetal-anomaly-scan',
    description: 'Second trimester detailed anatomy scan (18-22 weeks)',
    content: {
      concept: `# Fetal Anomaly Scan (18-22 Weeks)

## Overview

The fetal anomaly scan (also called Level II, morphology scan, or mid-trimester scan) is a systematic ultrasound examination performed at **18-22 weeks** to detect structural abnormalities.

## Timing

- **Optimal**: 18-22 weeks
- Earlier: Some structures not fully developed
- Later: Fetal position/size may limit visualization
- **20 weeks**: Often considered ideal

> 💎 **High Yield**: Detection rates vary by anomaly and operator experience. Training and standardization are critical.

## Systematic Approach

### 1. Head and Brain

**Measurements**
- Biparietal diameter (BPD)
- Head circumference (HC)

**Structures to Assess**

| Structure | Normal Finding | Abnormal |
|-----------|---------------|----------|
| Skull | Intact, oval | Lemon sign (spina bifida), cloverleaf |
| Cerebral ventricles | <10 mm atrium | Ventriculomegaly >10 mm |
| Cavum septum pellucidum | Present | Absent (holoprosencephaly, agenesis CC) |
| Cerebellum | Dumbbell shape | Banana sign (Chiari II), hypoplasia |
| Cisterna magna | 2-10 mm | Enlarged (Dandy-Walker) |
| Choroid plexus | Symmetric | Cysts (usually benign, associated T18) |

**Lemon and Banana Signs**
- **Lemon sign**: Frontal bossing (scalloped frontal bones)
- **Banana sign**: Curved cerebellum
- Both suggest open spina bifida with Chiari II malformation

### 2. Face

**Structures**
- Lips (rule out cleft)
- Nose
- Orbits (spacing, lens)
- Profile (micrognathia, nasal bone)

**Cleft Lip/Palate**
- Unilateral vs bilateral
- Lip only vs lip and palate
- Isolated vs syndromic

### 3. Spine

**Technique**
- Sagittal: Overall alignment, sacrum
- Transverse: Each vertebra - three ossification centers forming closed circle
- Coronal: Parallel lines

**Spina Bifida**
- Open defect visible on transverse view
- Skin covering absent
- Associated findings: Lemon sign, banana sign, ventriculomegaly

### 4. Heart

**Standard Views**

| View | Structures | Abnormalities Detected |
|------|------------|----------------------|
| Four-chamber | Atria, ventricles, septum, AV valves | VSD, AVSD, hypoplastic chambers |
| LVOT (5-chamber) | Left ventricle, aorta | Aortic stenosis, coarctation clues |
| RVOT (3-vessel) | Right ventricle, pulmonary artery | Pulmonary stenosis, ToF |
| 3-vessel view | Aorta, PA, SVC | Transposition, coarctation |
| 3-vessel-trachea | Above + trachea position | Right aortic arch |

**Normal Findings**
- Heart 1/3 of thorax
- Apex points left (45° angle)
- Equal-sized ventricles
- No significant regurgitation

> 💎 **High Yield**: Four-chamber view detects only 40-50% of cardiac anomalies. Outflow tracts are essential.

### 5. Thorax

- **Lungs**: Homogeneous echogenicity
- **Diaphragm**: Intact (stomach below, heart above)
- **CDH** (Congenital Diaphragmatic Hernia): Stomach/bowel in chest

### 6. Abdomen

| Structure | Normal | Abnormal |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| Stomach | Left upper quadrant, fluid-filled | Absent (esophageal atresia), right-sided (situs) |
| Kidneys | Paraspinal, bean-shaped | Absent (agenesis), cystic, dilated pelvis |
| Bladder | Midline pelvis | Megacystis, absent (BRA) |
| Cord insertion | Central, 3 vessels | Omphalocele, 2-vessel cord |
| Bowel | Not dilated | Dilated loops, echogenic |

### 7. Umbilical Cord

**Normal**: 3 vessels (2 arteries, 1 vein)

**Single Umbilical Artery (SUA)**
- Present in 0.5-1% of pregnancies
- 20-30% have associated anomalies
- Most common: Cardiac, renal
- Isolated SUA: Lower risk, consider detailed scan

### 8. Extremities

- All 4 limbs present
- 3 segments each (humerus/radius+ulna, femur/tibia+fibula)
- Hands and feet: 5 digits each
- Movement and position

**Abnormalities**
- Absent/shortened limbs (reduction defects)
- Positional abnormalities (clubfoot, rocker-bottom)
- Polydactyly, syndactyly

### 9. Placenta and Amniotic Fluid

**Placenta**
- Location (anterior, posterior, fundal, low-lying)
- Cord insertion (central, marginal, velamentous)
- Morphology (succenturiate lobe, abnormal thickness)

**Amniotic Fluid**
- Normal AFI: 5-25 cm
- Deepest vertical pocket: 2-8 cm

## Detection Rates by System

| Anomaly | Detection Rate |
|---------|---------------|
| Anencephaly | >99% |
| Spina bifida | 90% |
| Major cardiac | 50-60% |
| Diaphragmatic hernia | 60-70% |
| Gastroschisis | >95% |
| Renal agenesis | 80-90% |
| Limb reduction | 80% |

> 📌 Even with expert scanning, some anomalies are not detectable prenatally

## When Findings Are Abnormal

### Isolated Minor Abnormality
- Document and follow-up
- May be normal variant
- Consider soft markers in context

### Major Structural Anomaly
1. Detailed targeted ultrasound
2. Fetal echocardiography (if cardiac or marker)
3. Genetic counseling
4. Offer invasive testing (amniocentesis)
5. MRI if needed for brain/spine
6. Multidisciplinary discussion`,
      keyPoints: [
        'Optimal timing: 18-22 weeks (20 weeks ideal)',
        'Systematic approach: Head → Face → Spine → Heart → Chest → Abdomen → Limbs',
        'Four-chamber view detects only 40-50% of CHD - outflow tracts essential',
        'Lemon + Banana signs = open spina bifida',
        'Single umbilical artery: 20-30% have associated anomalies'
      ],
      examPrep: {
        summary: `**Anomaly Scan - Quick Review**

⏰ **Timing**: 18-22 weeks

🧠 **Brain**: Ventricles <10mm, CSP present, check for lemon/banana

❤️ **Heart**: 4-chamber + LVOT + RVOT + 3VT view

🦴 **Spine**: Sagittal + Transverse + Coronal

👶 **Limbs**: All present, 3 segments, 5 digits each

🔴 **Cord**: 3 vessels (SUA = detailed scan)

💧 **AFI**: Normal 5-25 cm`,
        mnemonics: [
          'Lemon + Banana = Spina bifida (Chiari II)',
